g.text: As a rule, only the Controller classes (yellow) ever update the
values that are stored in the model (app ctx blue).
Thus the views really only care about displaying the proper
information (fetched from the model, that's why many views
listen on events on the app) and emit events upon user action.
In the end, these events are caught by some of the controller
that take the appropriate action and updates the value stored
in the model if need be.
Note also that this diagram is not exhaustive but, for the sake
of clarity, leaves out some of the less important ui
